==Reception==
Famitsu rated this PSP game with a score of 35/40.<ref name=Famitsu>{{cite web|url=https://gematsu.com/2012/04/famitsu-review-scores-issue-1220 |title=Famitsu Review Scores: Issue 1220 |publisher=Gematsu |date=2012-04-17 |accessdate=2018-02-24}}</ref>

== Sequel ==
A sequel to the game, titled {{nihongo|''[[Conception II: Children of the Seven Stars]]''|コンセプションⅡ 七星の導きとマズルの悪夢}}, was released on August 22, 2013<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gematsu.com/2013/05/conception-ii-japanese-release-date-set |title=Conception II Japanese release date set |publisher=Gematsu |date=2013-05-22 |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref> for the [[Nintendo 3DS]] and  [[PlayStation Vita]], and August 15, 2016 on [[Steam (Software)|Steam]].<ref>{{cite web|author=Ishaan . August 19, 2013 . 11:00am |url=http://www.siliconera.com/2013/08/19/spike-shipping-more-copies-of-conception-ii-on-vita-than-3ds/ |title=Spike Shipping More Copies Of Conception II On Vita Than 3DS |publisher=Siliconera |date=2013-08-19 |accessdate=2013-08-23}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=A . August 17, 2016 . 04:02am |url=http://store.steampowered.com/app/458730/ |title=Game Conception 2 released on Steam |publisher=Steam |date=2016-08-17 |accessdate=2016-08-17}}</ref>

== Remaster ==
On September 17, 2018, Famitsu teased an article that would reveal a new ''Conception'' project. The next day on September 18, 2018, a remaster of the first ''Conception'' video game titled ''Conception Plus: Ore no Kodomo o Undekure!'' was announced to be shown at [[Tokyo Game Show]] 2018 for the [[PlayStation 4]].<ref>https://www.jp.playstation.com/events/tgs/title-all/</ref> It is being developed by Spike Chunsoft. No further details are known at this time.

