'''''We Have Issues''''' is an American comedy [[infotainment]] series which premiered on September 18, 2015, on the [[E!]] cable channel. The half-hour weekly show is hosted by comedians [[Julian McCullough]] and [[Annie Lederman]], who both discuss the biggest [[pop culture]] news of the week. A guest comedian is set to join the debate every week and "contribute to the hilarious he said/she said banter."<ref name="launch">{{cite press|url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2015/08/31/new-comedy-debate-series-we-have-issues-to-premiere-friday-september-18-on-e/455523/|title=New Comedy Debate Series 'We Have Issues' to Premiere Friday, September 18 on E!|first=Sara|last=Bibel|accessdate=September 2, 2015|date=August 31, 2015|work=[[TV by the Numbers]]|publisher=[[Tribune Digital Ventures]]}}</ref>

McCullough and Lederman have both appeared together on the late-night series ''[[@midnight]]'' and separately on various other panel talk shows, including ''[[World's Funniest]]'' and ''[[Chelsea Lately]]''.<ref name="cast">{{cite web|url=http://thecomicscomic.com/2015/08/27/julian-mccullough-and-annie-lederman-to-co-host-we-have-issues-weekly-series-on-e/|title=Julian McCullough and Annie Lederman to co-host "We Have Issues" weekly series on E!|accessdate=September 2, 2015|work=The Comic's Comic|first=Sean L.|last=McCarthy|date=August 27, 2015}}</ref>

== Hosts ==
* [[Julian McCullough]]
* [[Annie Lederman]]

==Broadcast==
The show debuted on the [[E!]] cable network in the United States on September 18, 2015, after another pop culture news-based series ''[[The Soup]]''. The show continues to air at 10:30/9:30pm [[Effects of time zones on North American broadcasting|ET/PT]] on Friday nights.<ref name="launch"/> Internationally, the series premiered on [[E! Australia]] on September 23, 2015.<ref name="Sept21Fox">{{cite web|work=The Green Room|first=Charles|last=Purcell|url=http://community.foxtel.com.au/t5/Foxtel-Blog/NEW-THIS-WEEK-Sep-21-A-Place-To-Call-Home-Emmys-Wahlburgers-Rick/ba-p/91192|title=New This Week (Sep 21): A Place To Call Home, Emmys, Wahlburgers, Rick Stein, Rugby World Cup & more|date=September 18, 2015|accessdate=September 19, 2015|archivedate=September 18, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150918030841/http://community.foxtel.com.au/t5/Foxtel-Blog/NEW-THIS-WEEK-Sep-21-A-Place-To-Call-Home-Emmys-Wahlburgers-Rick/ba-p/91192}}</ref>

